Product Description

Clinically Developed DHT Blocker for Men and Women to Support Hair Regrowth

*AHLA does not offer warranties or guarantees on results or provide any remedy for any brand that it accepts. Results vary.

**Outcomes Vary. These before and after photos were taken in our clinics using a variety of Advanced Trichology products and some clinical case regimens used are only offered by our clinical team.

Natural Formula developed in Hair Loss Clinics for Maximum Hair Growth

The DHT Blocker with Immune Support was created to address common problems that no other DHT Blocker Supplement can address. Numerous ancillary health issues can impact a person’s hair growth beyond DHT such as: stress, malabsorption, poor diet, medications, gut health, and yeast overgrowth. Our Proprietary formula is the only nutritional supplement that can address them all.​

  • Targets hair loss by blocking DHT activity*
  • Targets male and female pattern hair loss and supports hormonal balance*
  • Encourages new hair follicle growth by boosting blood circulation*
  • Heightens the flow of oxygen and nutrients to hair follicles*
  • Helps collagen fibers in the hair follicles interlock*
  • Heightens the production of keratin and collagen*
  • Targets sebum-related hair loss*
  • Provides hair growth-enhancing nutrients*
  • Scavenges free radicals linked to hair loss*

Exceptional Outcomes for Men and Women with Genetic Hair Loss

Best for Women with: Hair Loss that began after turning 30, hair loss that began after taking birth control or hormone replacement therapy, a family history of hair loss including men or women with hair loss, and/or hair loss that is exclusively on the top scalp.

SPECIFIC RESULTS FOR WOMEN: Supports Fuller Healthy Hair Growth, DHT Blocker for Women, Supports Hormonal Health, Supports Better Metabolism, and Lessens Bloating.

Best for Men with: Hair Loss that occurred after turning 17, a family history of hair loss including men or women with hair loss, and/or hair loss that is exclusively on the top scalp in the typical male pattern loss area.

SPECIFIC RESULTS FOR MEN: Supports Fuller Healthy Hair Growth, DHT Blocker for Men, Supports Prostate Health, Enhances effectiveness of Medical DHT Blockers, and Supports Balanced Digestion.

“I have been developing Advanced Trichology Products in my Clinics for 19 Years. I have specifically developed the DHT Blocker to be the most Powerful and Efficient DHT Blocker Supplement available to date. No matter what, my goal is simple. It’s to provide you with a hair loss product that works.”

William Gaunitz FWTS Certified Trichologist Founder Advanced Trichology (Member No: 2014-0239)

MAXIMUM HAIR GROWTH BENEFITS: The DHT Blocker with Immune Support is specifically designed to Block DHT (dy-hydro-testosterone), Improve Digestion, Enhance Nutrient Absorption, and Boost Your Immune System to Grow More Hair.

MORE THAN JUST A POWERFUL DHT BLOCKER: The DHT Blocker with Immune Support is totally Unique and is the only hair loss supplement EVER to combine the most potent DHT Blockers with antioxidants and proven clinical digestive support.

DIRECTIONS: Take (2) two capsules in the morning and (2) two capsules at night with food to experience the results. For people who are more sensitive, you may start with (1) one in the morning and (1) one a night with food.

FOR BEST OUTCOME: Use together with Hairstem Shampoo and NutraM Topical Hair Serum.

All we do is Support Hair Regrowth

Important information

Safety Information

If you are pregnant, have allergies to grapes, green tea, caffeine, probiotics, or any of the ingredients, do not take the product. Discontinue use and consult your doctor if any adverse reactions occur. Before using, talk to your doctor if you: are currently taking blood thinners or medicines, are allergic to any medicine (prescription or over-the-counter or dietary supplements) or plan to become pregnant while using this product, are breast-feeding, or have currently or in the past any severe digestive or prostate issues. Some digestive discomfort has been reported when taken on an empty stomach. This product does contain prebiotic chicory root and lactobacillus acidophilus probiotic: some intestinal gas or bloating, upset stomach, and diarrhea have been reported for this ingredient for those who are sensitive. May contain some trace amounts of caffeine in the green tea extract. This product is labeled to United States standards and may differ from similar products sold elsewhere in its ingredients, labeling and allergen warnings. Discontinue use and consult your doctor if any adverse reactions occur. Capsule size -00- (average fill 650 mg)

Indications

Do not take if pregnant. Do not take if you have allergies to grapes or to any of the ingredients. Some digestive discomfort has been reported when taken on an empty stomach. This product does contain prebiotic chicory root and lactobacillus acidophilus probiotic: some intestinal gas or bloating, upset stomach, and diarrhea have been reported for this ingredient for those who are sensitive. If you have a history of severe digestive issues, talk to your physician prior to use.

Ingredients

Zinc (as Zinc Oxide) 15mgs DHT Blocker Proprietary Blend 1390mgs *Saw Palmetto Berry Extract (Standardized to contain 45% Fatty Acids) (Serenoa repens), Green Tea Leaf Extract (Standardized to Contain 90% Polyphenols, 60% Catechins, and 45% EGCG), Stinging Nettle Root(Urtica dioicia), L-Lysine, Grape Seed Extract (Standardized to Contain 95% Proanthocyanidins) (Vitis vinefera), Pygeum Bark (Pygeum africanum), Pumpkin Seed Extract (Curcubita maxima) Immune/Digestive Proprietary Blend 525mgs *Lactobacillus Acidophilus (15 Billion/CFU), Grapefruit Seed Extract (Citrus paradise), Chicory Root 4:1 Extract (Cichorium intybus)

Directions

Take two capsules twice daily before meals.

I did a Dutch complete hormone test and it indicated that even though my testosterone is sorta low, it was being converted into DHT via the 5 alpha reductase pathway. It’s important to know that this will only help if you have DHT issues. Hair loss can be many things, so it’s important to test your hormones, thyroid, adrenals etc. I was losing so much hair like in the picture that has the 19 which was the 19th of March. I started this product on March 16. In less than a week my hair shed was half of what it was. In the next few days it was even less and has stayed that way for the past 2.5 weeks. I also was having some acne issues, nothing ever too crazy though like some pimples on my jawline and then texture on my forehead and a few starting on my shoulder blades. My skin had cleared up and it’s so smooth already! I was shocked. I do take some other Adaptogens like ashwaganda and some mushroom extracts but it never slowed the hair loss until I used this. If you suspect you have any DHT symptoms like I have, I can’t recommend this enough!

ILikeThings
4.0 out of 5 stars Dht, folligrow, and the serum
Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2023
Verified Purchase
** 30 day update below.
**47 day update at bottom
**60 day (3/14/23) at bottom.
Hairloss is stressful, scary, and heartbreaking so I wanted to provide an early review so others, like myself, can have a bit of a sigh of relief. If you are like me spending hours reading through reviews to see WHEN we can see some type of goodness, then continue reading.
I'm on day 14 of Dht blocker and folligrow, and day 4 of the serum. It's too soon for any growth update, but the shedding has drastically reduced. I take them as directed minus with food in the morning as im not hungry at 7am. 15 days ago, my shower drain would be hair clogged within minutes of getting in the shower, now the hair in the drain is about a quarter of what it was. 15 days ago I would brush my hair or run my fingers through it and I would hair hair covering my shirt, the floor, counters, brush/hands, everything. Today, only a few hairs in the brush. I'm very hopeful this product will help.
My only issue so far is that if I do take the pills in the evening (5pm or later) I notice I can't fall asleep. I do not drink anything with caffeine in it after 10am anymore so I know it's nothing I'm drinking causing this and the only thing new are these pills. I am currently experimenting with the times I take the second set.
I have recently tested my thyroid and found it's very underactive again which is likely causing my hair loss (plus perimenopause). I will keep taking these along with the two other products and update this review at the 30 or 45 day mark.

I hope this review helps others looking for signs of hope. I wish more people would leave longer detailed reviews on things like this.
30 days: technically 29 but nothing major will happen overnight LOL
I stopped the serum for now because of two things- it's winter and it's super dry in my house so I don't want to wash my hair everyday and have to blow dry it. Kind of defeats the purpose of what I'm doing, and I started red and nir light therapy around day 17. It looks like my wispy short hairs (either breakage or new from before starting this) are getting longer. Shedding is unbelievably less than ever. Like it's been YEARS since I've experienced "normal" shedding. LOL I just woke up and I'm a crazy sleeper. I took my sad, thin little braid out and brushed my hair and there were zero hairs on my shirt and a couple in the brush. My skin looks nicer. Haven't gotten my normal hormonal cystic acne this month but do have a few tzone breakouts - which I normally don't get.
I woke up to a lot of dandruff/skin turnover this morning but it could be because I skipped my dandruff shampoo this week. When I blow dried my hair last night, there were a few hairs on the ground, but nothing like before. A month ago, I was like a dandelion in the wind lol
Because of all this, I leave my 4 stars. It stopped the shedding, y'all. I mean... that right there is impressive and awesome in itself.
I'll be back in a month!

**47 days.
While my hair is not shedding as stated above, my period this time around lasted 12 days. Mostly spotting but I had to do AM pills only for a week in order for the spotting to stop (foligrow and dht blockers). Idk which one caused the extended bleeding if either of them did. I've also noticed that these seem to constipate me a bit. I thought I just had to get used to them but when I lowered the dose my BMs were more frequent again. Now I'm back too tiny to no BMs, then clogged, then a full day or two of stomach aches and bathroom runs. Sigh. I have another period coming up this week. If I bleed longer again, I will have to cut back both and hope it doesn't mess up my progress.
My hair does seem fuller (to me) and is growing in length quicker it seems. I honestly don't think I see new growth, but I do have hairs ranging from a quarter inch to half inch all over the top of my head. I feel these may just be breakage hairs growing out? I would think any NEW growth would be just starting to pop out now or soon.
**60 days
Stopped dht blocker a few days ago due to excessive bleeding. I'm still taking the foligrow vitamins and I'm hoping it's enough to keep the hair growth. Within the last week I've really noticed a ton of 1cm hairs all over my head. I uploaded a photo of my part and I feel like there's a pretty decent difference in the two. My hair feels thicker and looks fuller. Fingers crossed the vitamins are enough to keep the growth going.

Anti-Chris
5.0 out of 5 stars 100% Honest Review + Total Transparency
Reviewed in the United States on March 1, 2020
Verified Purchase
My 100% Honest Review with Total Transparency-

I bought this when I noticed my hair was starting to fall out in extraordinary amounts. I remember when it began Jan 28, and I’m talking bags and bags of hair that have falling.
Ever seen the movie, The Craft? Remember when the popular blonde girl was being so mean to one of the girls in the coven and she puts a spell that makes all the blonde girls hair fall out. After their swim meet, in the locker room the girl from the coven finds the blonde girl sitting in the shower sobbing... She’s 90% bald. While touching her falling hair she says to the witch, “It just keeps falling out!”

Okay, my situation isn’t That bad, but that’s how I felt, since it has been falling out in clumps, every time I wash it, when it never had before. Like most, I made things worse by going online looking for probable causes, which only made me more stressed out,
but my dermatologist appt. was two weeks away, and I couldn't just wait around without trying to do Something about it. The thing about hair loss is that there are a number is reasons causing it to fall... So, I jumped the gun before a diagnosis. C’mon guys, I’m only human!
Enter Advanced Trichology DHT Blocker w/ Immune Support- yes, it’s ok the pricey side, but if that’s a concern, keep in mind- they come with a 100% satisfactory guarantee or your money back. PLUS, inside their bottle is a generous offer upon registering for a free bottle of their other products.
**NOTE WHAT I REALLY APPRECIATE ABOUT THIS IS THAT THE OFFER IS NOT IN EXCHANGE FOR A 4+ STAR REVIEW.
So, know that’s NOT why I’m writing this.....

They recommend taking 4 per day, which
I couldn’t do. They were hard on MY tummy w/o food. I dry heaved a couple times immediately after taking two in the morning w/o food, but I PERSONALLY have a sensitive stomach, and because of my situation, my stomach was already in knots regardless. After eating in the afternoon I’d take two and I’d try to take one more at night as well- and my tummy didn’t hurt.

Then I saw my doctor... she prescribed me Spironolactone, (a diuretic for high blood pressure that also helps hair loss by fighting androgens). Which I assumed would work immediately. It actually can take up to 3-6 months to start working, and that’s only IF your hair is falling out due to DHT and/or Androgenic Alopecia, but my doctor says that mine is falling due to some serious emotional stress that lasted several months a couple months ago. I asked her if I should continue taking the supplements and she said that although it wouldn’t hurt, if I was struggling to take the recommended dosage (4 pd), then I probably shouldn’t, since it most likely won’t help my personal situation. She said, “You can take as many supplements as you want and your hair will still fall because you’re too stressed out.” She suggested meditation, 20 minutes of daily sun exposure (since I’m D3 deficient) and she urged me to eliminate refined sugars processed foods from my diet, and drink plenty of organic homemade bone broth.

So, I can’t say that Advanced Trichology DHT Blocker works, but not because it isn’t a quality supplement, but because My hair loss isn’t due to high levels of DHT, and since my tummy is extra sensitive right from from stress, it’s unable to tolerate supplements.

I believe that this is a quality supplement. Its highly recommended by many both on and off Amazon. So, I’d say it’s definitely worth trying, especially if your hair loss is DHT related. However, I advise getting bloodwork done first and a diagnosis prior to taking anything, especially since supplementing can deliver inaccurate lab results, especially if you don’t tell your doctor exactly what you’re taking.
It’s crazy to think how far science has come... couples can decide what color eyes they want their child to have, through genetic modification. If you have $5,000, you can permanently change your eye color from brown to blue or from brown to green through a non-invasive 30 second procedure that’s similar to Lasik eye surgery, and yet science still hasn’t been able to cure hair loss!

Until then, I’m grateful for company’s like Advanced Trichology for providing us with much needed hope.
